<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_list\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_List all created conversations._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Retrieve a list of conversation entities sorted by creation time.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<SectionContent

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.list({});

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

Python

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_list_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.list(page=0, page_size=100)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

##### response_format \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_list_responses_200_application-json_modelconversation_completion_args_completionargs_response_format\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Specify the format that the model must output. By default it will use `\{ "type": "text" \}`. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_object" \}` enables JSON mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON. When using JSON mode you MUST also instruct the model to produce JSON yourself with a system or a user message. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_schema" \}` enables JSON schema mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON and follows the schema you provide.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.start({
    inputs: "<value>",
  });

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_python"
  tags={{"codeSample":"python"}}
>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.start(inputs="<value>", stream=False)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Specify the format that the model must output. By default it will use `\{ "type": "text" \}`. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_object" \}` enables JSON mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON. When using JSON mode you MUST also instruct the model to produce JSON yourself with a system or a user message. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_schema" \}` enables JSON schema mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON and follows the schema you provide.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve a conversation information._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve a conversation entity with its attributes.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

TypeScript

<SectionContent

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.get({
    conversationId: "<id>",
  });

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_get_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\} \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.append({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationAppendRequest: {
      inputs: [],
    },
  });

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_python"
  tags={{"codeSample":"python"}}
>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[], stream=False, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

##### response_format \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_request_completion_args_completionargs_response_format\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Specify the format that the model must output. By default it will use `\{ "type": "text" \}`. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_object" \}` enables JSON mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON. When using JSON mode you MUST also instruct the model to produce JSON yourself with a system or a user message. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_schema" \}` enables JSON schema mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON and follows the schema you provide.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/history \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all entries in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the entries belonging to that conversation. The entries are sorted in the order they were appended, those can be messages, connectors or function_call.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.getHistory({
    conversationId: "<id>",
  });

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_history(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/messages \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all messages in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the messages belonging to that conversation. This is similar to retrieving all entries except we filter the messages only.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.getMessages({
    conversationId: "<id>",
  });

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages_code-samples_python"
  tags={{"codeSample":"python"}}
>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_messages(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.restart({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationRestartRequest: {
      inputs: "<value>",
      fromEntryId: "<id>",
    },
  });

  console.log(result);
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_python"

Python

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", from_entry_id="<id>", stream=False, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Specify the format that the model must output. By default it will use `\{ "type": "text" \}`. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_object" \}` enables JSON mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON. When using JSON mode you MUST also instruct the model to produce JSON yourself with a system or a user message. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_schema" \}` enables JSON schema mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON and follows the schema you provide.

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.startStream({
    inputs: [
      {
        object: "entry",
        type: "agent.handoff",
        previousAgentId: "<id>",
        previousAgentName: "<value>",
        nextAgentId: "<id>",
        nextAgentName: "<value>",
      },
    ],
  });

  for await (const event of result) {
    // Handle the event
    console.log(event);
  }
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_python"
  tags={{"codeSample":"python"}}
>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.start_stream(inputs=[
        {
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "function.result",
            "tool_call_id": "<id>",
            "result": "<value>",
        },
    ], stream=True)

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

<ExpandablePropertyTitle slot="title">

##### response_format \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_request_completion_args_completionargs_response_format\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Specify the format that the model must output. By default it will use `\{ "type": "text" \}`. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_object" \}` enables JSON mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON. When using JSON mode you MUST also instruct the model to produce JSON yourself with a system or a user message. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_schema" \}` enables JSON schema mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON and follows the schema you provide.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.appendStream({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationAppendStreamRequest: {
      inputs: "<value>",
    },
  });

  for await (const event of result) {
    // Handle the event
    console.log(event);
  }
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_python"
  tags={{"codeSample":"python"}}
>

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", stream=True, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<CodeSampleTabbedSection>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_typescript"
  tags={{"codeSample":"typescript"}}
>

TypeScript

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<CodeSample>

```typescript
import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "MISTRAL_API_KEY",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.restartStream({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationRestartStreamRequest: {
      inputs: [
        {
          object: "entry",
          type: "message.input",
          role: "assistant",
          content: "<value>",
          prefix: false,
        },
      ],
      fromEntryId: "<id>",
    },
  });

  for await (const event of result) {
    // Handle the event
    console.log(event);
  }
}

run();

```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<CodeSampleTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_python"
  tags={{"codeSample":"python"}}

Python

</CodeSampleTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[
        {
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "message.input",
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "<value>",
            "prefix": False,
        },
    ], from_entry_id="<id>", stream=True, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

<ExpandablePropertyTitle slot="title">

##### response_format \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_request_completion_args_completionargs_response_format\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Specify the format that the model must output. By default it will use `\{ "type": "text" \}`. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_object" \}` enables JSON mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON. When using JSON mode you MUST also instruct the model to produce JSON yourself with a system or a user message. Setting to `\{ "type": "json_schema" \}` enables JSON schema mode, which guarantees the message the model generates is in JSON and follows the schema you provide.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>
